<br>
Erudites of all class believe they are the honed perfection of the human race, more inteligent and superior, on parr with elves but in a different way, elves live for long lifespans and learn many things, erudites have a short lifespan so work harder to reach there knowledge.. so in there eyes are superior than elves. <br>
An erudite shadowknight would have a strong discut for the palace of erudin for outcasting necromancy, they are devoted to the studies of necromancy.<br>
<br>
Bertoxxulous, humans of bertoxxulous work to bring there deity into this work so he can claim it as his own, working on all forms of death and undeath, they are interested in means to further there cause and bring trouble to those who interfere... dont mess with the shrine and they leave you alone.<br>
<br>
Innoruuk, humans. Following hate, but in alliance with neriak who use them, and they know it.. but try to get as much out of there dealings with the dark elf as they can. The human was the first race to become a shadowknight.<br>
<br>
Dark elf, while following there race, they wage war on the races that cast them down, elves, halfings... look at the humans like they are fire beetles and have some other strange views.<br>
They see there own race as supeiror, there deity as 'the' most worthy and powerfull deity, yet hate consumes them and drives there chaotic world. They enjoy bringing hate to others in any form.<br>
<br>
Cazic thule, trolls. Trolls have simple minds... they like to bully things,odds in there favour etc... they like to smash and bash and taunt and kill, and love to eat there victims later... they are not evil as a choice.. its just the way they are, they are born with an inate ablity to bully.<br>
<br>
Ogres and rallos zek. These believe that might is right, neutral. they like to fight and fight anything, anywere for the challenge. Most other races hate ogres because ogres always start a fight, better to deal with them asap when they are spotted entering citys.<br>
<br>
Its very different, and with a bit of reserch, how npc react, talk, factions, allies etc you can find some usefull roleplaying. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utiestooakey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tiesto Oakey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator<br>Shadowknight who says Ni!</span><br>  Posts: 188<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 8:11:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1133.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bet you havent heard this question before</span><hr size=1> Shaman. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jaelyndimathe>Jaelyn DiMathe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 9:10:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1133.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ranger</span><hr size=1> 2 votes for Ranger - <br>
<br>
A valuable asset to any group, especially on this server.  I've been part of many groups now in LOIO, and the ability to track farther than most people can see and continously pull in yellows and reds mean non-stop XP and carnage.  True, the ability is much less useful in a dungeon, but in an outgroup it can't beat.  Add in our buffs, bow skills, dual wield, double attack, disarm, risoste, SOW, and extremely useful high level group buffs and we're a class that's useful with almost any group.  As for solo, a skilled ranger can solo to 50+, once you know where and what to hunt <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So, while you're deciding what to play, don't overlook Rangers.<br>
<br>
Jaelyn DiMathe<br>
24th Season tracker of the True God <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ublakkon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>blakkon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 10:51:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1133.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Um shaman are in the top three soloers....</span><hr size=1> At higher levels no one solo's better in a  dungeon.  When bored on my old server I would do things like break and hold the king room in lguk solo....  Shaman have soloed dragons in Western wastes, shaman have soloed Juggernauts in Old Sebilis. However, they grow into their powers over the course of their career so are often overlooked.  Shaman is a great group character, and they can solo from day one to level 60, if you play a barbarian they can be good aligned.  And at lvl 9 they are able to travel anywhere you can run with Spirit of the Wolf. <br>
<br>
But.. I think a Ranger or Palladin could also fit you.  Though of the two, Rangers are the better soloers.  Palladins can solo but it gets fairly slow in mid levels.  Rangers with snare, animal based fear, and bow-kiting can solo all the way to 60 with care.  I also think they are a good group character, but have severe agro problems post 50.  <br>
<br>
I have played a Shaman to 55 and a ranger to 47 and a horde of other characters in past lives... I rerolled the Shaman when I moved here.....<br>
